Panera delivery is a bunch of BS.  Two days in a row, yes I gave them a second chance, we ordered Panera Aventura to be delivered.  After waiting more than 2 hours, we called to speak with the manager that simply said that they don't know what happened to the order.  Then we received a notification that it was delivered but to a completely wrong apartment that is clearly marked.  We called to dispute the charge and Panera simply said that food was made and delivered. The next day, we ordered. Same thing, almost 2 hours go by and of course we are steaming by then.  The manager again said he wasn't sure where the order was. Sometime after calling multiple times, we finally got a notification that the order was delivered...to the wrong apartment, completely different from our apartment and different from yesterday's mess up.  It is as if they do not care where they throw the food and take a picture and leave and Panera has the nerve to criminally charge for it for an order that was never received.  The management team at Aventura has no care in the world about the quality of service and do not care to rectify their clearly bad delivery service who is billed through Uber but Uber told us that it is the Panera delivery team.  It is so sad that any other Panera we have been to, we haven't had issues.  I am surprised that these people working here are still employed because there are plenty of people out of work that have the care to try and live up to what we thought was a decent standard of restaurant.
